IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: The Mission of God's Pantry Food Bank is to reduce hunger in Kentucky through community cooperation
IRS990.MissionDescription: The Mission of God's Pantry Food Bank is to reduce hunger in Kentucky through community cooperation making the best possible use of all available resources.
IRS990.Description: God's pantry distributed 17,080,704 million pounds of food to more than 320 non-profit agencies serving 50 central and eastern Ky counties. More than 19,768 households in Fayette county received the Emergency Food Box Program.

Activity2.Description: The Fayette County Emergency Food Box Program serves clients directly through the distribution of a seven day supply of food thru five pantry locations. Households served was 19,768.

Activity3.Description: The Mobile and Satellite Pantry Programs provide temporary emergency food pantry service to households in counties with few or no pantry service. It also works to foster the development of permanent food pantry programs in those counties. We use our Gap Analysis and pounds per person in poverty number to determine which counties are underserved. Households served was 7,255.

ActivityOther.Description: The Sharing Thanksgiving Program is a boxed Thanksgiving dinner along with a turkey, eggs and butter. All households are referred by a social service agency. Baskets distributed to households 4,119.
